7... Nge7 8. Bd2 { This will generally transpose to other lines. } 8... O-O 9.
Qc1 Rb8
{ This is often a very good semi-waiting move that we will see come up again and again. Black moves off of the long diagonal and often prepares ...b5.   After  9...Be6  ,  10.Ng5  is possible, although we could respond with  10...Bc8  and it's not clear what White has achieved. }
10. Rb1 a6 11. a3 b5 12. cxb5 axb5 13. b4 cxb4 14. axb4 d5
{ Black has more space, can activate his final pieces and start some play on the kingside. }
