11. Ne1
{ The knight heads to c2 to support the b4 advance, and it may also go to e3 and d5. But now we can play .. .Be6 without any harassment from White's knight. The alternatives are not very dangerous. }
11... Be6 { Now White has a typical choice - allow ...d5, or prevent it? } 12.
Nd5 b5 { Black breaks first. } 13. Nxe7+ Nxe7 14. cxb5 Rxb5 15. b4 axb4 16.
axb4 cxb4 17. Rxb4 Rxb4 18. Bxb4 Qb6
{ If anything, Black has some chances to take the initiative, as the e1-knight is in White's way. }
