13... bxc6
{ Black's structure is wrecked, but White had to give up his king's best defender. Both sides should keep an eye on Black's breaks with ...c4 and ...e4, even as pawn sacrifices. }
14. Na4 Nxa4 15. Qxa4 O-O { This certainly looks like more fun for Black. } 16.
Nc4 e4 { With the following idea. } 17. dxe4 Qd4 18. Nb6 { Forced. } 18... Rab8
19. Qxd4 { This avoids a direct loss, but it corrects Black's pawn structure. }
19... cxd4 { with the bishop pair and a huge initiative. } *

