14. Na4 Nxa4 15. Qxa4 O-O { This certainly looks like more fun for Black. } 16.
Bd2 Qd4 { Taking aim at the b2-pawn with  16...e4!?  looks good too. } 17. Nc4
Bxc4 18. Qxc4 Qxc4 19. dxc4 e4 20. Rab1 a4
{ The b2-pawn is at least as weak as Black's doubled c-pawns. } 21. Be3 Rfb8
22. Bxc5 Rb3
{ Black had enduring pressure in Eckert - Kavutskiy, Saint Louis 2016. } *

