6. Nge2 O-O
{ There are various move orders. Sometimes Black tries  6...d6  with the idea  7.O-O  h5!?   White could just play the more accurate  7.d3  though. }
7. d3
{ This looks best - remember we played ... d6 quickly in the same setup with Black. }
7... d6
{ If  7...Ne8  8.Be3  d6  9.d4!  As we would do ourselves with colours reversed. }
8. O-O a6
{ Again avoiding  8...Ne8  9.Be3!  Nc7   or  9...Nd4  10.Rb1!  just as we would play in the reversed position.  10.d4 }
9. h3 { Avoiding  9.Be3  Ng4  . } 9... Rb8 10. a4 Bd7
{ Or  10...Ne8  11.Be3  when Black has generally prevented  d4 with the 'wrong' knight:   11...Nd4   but there is also the interesting  11...b5!?  which is not even a pawn sacrifice:  12.axb5  axb5  13.Nxb5  Nc7=   or  13.cxb5  Nd4 }
11. Be3 e5
{ I made this up at the board, and it's pretty good! This move is also not considered in Marin's series on the English Opening for White. We now have a 'double Botvinnnik' of sorts, but Black's knight is on the f6-square. It could be considered to be misplaced, but I do not think matters are so simple.   In this structure, pushing the f-pawn is not always so great, as a subsequent exf5/...exf4 opens the diagonal for a blocked bishop. Decades of playing the Botvinnik setup has also taught me to be careful with the e7-knight, as it is not always so manoeuverable. The f6-knight has potential pathways to improvement, most notably with ...Ne8-c7.   Lastly, in this pawn structure, the move Be3/Be6 can be premature, as Nd5/...Nd4 can be annoying because capturing with a knight would lose a piece. Here White's bishop is already on e3, while our bishop is on the d7-square. I know sometimes this means it's more passive, but here I'll say it's more flexible! }
12. f4 { It's good to see how to play after this. } 12... exf4
{ 12...Nd4  is fine too, but let's increase the scope of the g7-bishop. } 13.
Nxf4 Ne8
{ From here the knight will go to c7, when it may trade off a knight on d5, or come to e6 and d4. }
14. Nfd5 Nc7 15. Nxc7 Qxc7 16. Nd5 Qd8
{ All of the minor pieces are good, except for White's sad g2-bishop. } *

