11. Ne3 Rc8 12. Rb1 b6 13. Nd5 Nd7 14. h4
{ Trying to stir up some trouble against a low rated FM. Black also looks fine after  14.Rb5  Qxa2  or  14.Be2  Nce5 }
14... Nc5 { 14...Nce5  is a good alternative. } 15. Qc2 Qa4
{ Thematic. These days the engine likes  15...f5!?  with strong counterplay. }
16. Qxa4 Nxa4 17. h5 Rg8 18. hxg6 hxg6 19. Bg5 Nc5
{ 19...f6  is fine too, because  20.Bxf6  exf6  21.Nxf6+  Ke7  22.Nxg8+  Bxg8  does not work out well for White. The rooks have no entry and those c-pawns will likely fall. }
20. Kd2 Kd7 21. Be2 Rh8
{ Smirin - Vigorito, Philadelphia 1997. I had just beaten three GM's in a row - for the first and last time! - and made a very comfortable draw here, securing my first IM norm. }
