10. c5 Ne4
{ In Grandmaster Repertoire 10: The Tarrasch Defence, Aagaard and Ntrilis consider this position reversed - @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  d5  2.c4  e6  3.Nc3  c5  4.cxd5  exd5  5.Nf3  Nc6  6.g3  Nf6  7.Bg2  Be7  8.O-O  O-O  9.Be3  c4  10.Ne5  - and they give “  10...h6!  ”. Here the analogous move - h2-h3 - has already been played. So what should White do with the extra tempo? }
