16... Qxe7 17. Bxe7 Kxe7
{ White wins right away after  17...Rxe7??  18.Ng5+  . } 18. Nd5+ Kf8
{ Black loses to some interesting geometry after  18...Nxd5  19.Qxd5  Bxf3  20.Re1+!  Kf8  21.Qxf3+  Kg8  22.Qd5+  Kh8  23.Rxe8+  Rxe8  and now  24.Qxa5  +- covers the  e1  square! }
19. Qd2 Bxf3 20. Nc7
{ The f3-bishop and a5-knight are both under attack, so White should take this chance to grab some more material. }
20... Bc6
{ One annotator suggested  20...Rad8  21.Qf4+!  Kg8  22.Nxe8  Rxe8  23.Qxf3  Bxb2  claiming Black was better here, but after  24.Rd1±  it is White who is better, as it is difficult for Black to get his minor pieces coordinated. }
21. Qxa5 Kg8 22. Nxe8 Rxe8 23. Re1 { Now Black should play } 23... Rf8
{ as pointed out by Delchev. } 24. Qxa7 { This would lose immediately to }
24... Bd4 { threatening both ...Bxf2+ and ...Ra8. } *

