bxc3 Qc7 13. Bg2 e5
{ Blocking e4-e5 and taking a stand on the dark-squares.   13...b6?!  14.e5!  causes problems.   The older  13...O-O  is quite playable though. If allowed, Black will follow up with ...b6 to prevent c4-c5. Then ...Be6 or ...Ba6 will lay siege to the c4-pawn. }
