11. Bf4 Ng6 12. Bd6 { White at least prevents Black from castling. } 12... bxc5
13. a3 Bxc3+ 14. bxc3
{ Now the c5-pawn is under attack, but Black has a clever response. } 14... a5
{ An excellent move that prepares ...c4 while avoiding the response Nb3-a5.   Instead  14...Nxe4?  backfires after  15.fxe4  Qxe4+  16.Kf2  Qxh1  17.Bg2  Qxd1  18.Rxd1  and the a8-rook is trapped!   Trading bishops with  14...Ba6?!  is not a bad idea in itself, but  15.Bxa6  Qxa6  16.Nxc5  regains the pawn with advantage. }
15. Nxc5 { Not  15.Bxc5?  a4  -+ } 15... Nd5 16. exd5 Qxd6
{ White is just scraping to hold the balance. } *

