{ This is not only an obvious move, but it's an essential one because Black will often need to meet e4 with ...Nc3. }
18. Qd4 f6
{ It is very important that the a4-bishop guards both the black queen and the d1-square. This position has been seen a few times in practice. Ori Kobo played it twice with White. }
19. Bh3 { This tries to pressure the e6-pawn. } 19... Kf7
{ Going here was part of Black's plan anyway. } 20. Bb2 Rhd8 21. Rac1 Ne7 22.
Qg4 Ng6 { Kobo - Greenfeld, Maalot Tarshiha 2018. } *

