9. Qa4
{ This wild looking move was first played by Aronian in a game against Leko. White simply allows ...Qxf2+. }
9... Qxf2+
{ Ok, this is very obvious, and yet I adorn it with  !? Generally this immediate capture has been considered to be inaccurate, but I think it is a good move. Leko took 80 minutes @@StartBracket@@!@@EndBracket@@ on  9...g5  and this is still the main line. After  10.Bxe5  Leko played  10...Nxe5  , which is playable but leads to a slight edge for White. Instead  10...Qxf2+  leads to a forced draw. If you want to memorize this out, the games are easy to find. Shankland - Leko, Tsaghkadzro 2015 is one of them. If Black forgets something though, he loses - so does White for that matter I suppose! Look up the game Nakamura - Karjakin, Zurich 2015 for a fatal memory lapse. }
10. Kd1 Kd8 { This guards the c7-square and ...Ne3+ will come next. } *

