{ The most natural.  12...Qe8!?  is an interesting computer suggestion. } 13.
e3 Be6 14. Qd2 Qa5
{ Hitting the g5-bishop and increasing the pressure on the c3-knight. } 15. Bh4
{ This was played in an old game Suba - Portisch, Thessaloniki 1984. Now the calm: }
15... Rac8
{ with ...g5! and ...Rfd8 coming, is too much for White to handle. For example: }
16. Be2 g5 17. Bg3 Rfd8 18. Qc1 Nd4
{ With such development it's not surprising that there is a brutal tactical solution. }
19. exd4 Bxc3+ 20. bxc3 Rxc3 21. Qd2
{ White would be winning here if it wasn't for } 21... Rxd4
{ And White's position collapses. } *

