{ MVL exchanged queens here once, and Black had compensation for the pawn. However, this move is even stronger. }
16. e4 Qb3 17. Qc1 Nd4
{ The logical  17...Be6  is also good and has been used successfully in practice. The text looks even stronger. }
18. Nxd4 Rxd4
{ Now ...Be6 and ...Rad8 would give Black a great attack. White does not have the luxury of worrying about the e4-pawn. }
19. Be2 Rxe4 20. Qd2 { Protecting the bishop and hoping to get castled. } 20...
Qb5 { Not so fast! } 21. O-O-O { What else? } 21... Qc5+
{ Black is unable to take on  e2  , as  21...Rxe2  runs into  22.Qxe2!  because of the back rank issues. }
22. Qc3 Qxc3+ 23. bxc3 Be6 { With a slightly better endgame. } *

