7. e3 Qa5 { Now ...Ne4 is on the agenda. } 8. Bxf6
{ This is a strange move. White gives up a bishop without even doubling Black's pawns. }
8... Bxf6 9. Qd2 O-O { Black could exchange on d4 first too. } 10. Be2 Nxd4 11.
exd4 d5 12. cxd5 exd5 13. O-O Be6
{ This leaves Black with the bishop pair and the sunny side of equality. } *

