{ This looks the most challenging. } 8... axb5 9. Bd6 Qa5+
{ Black must avoid  9...Ne4?!  10.Bg2  Qa5+?  11.b4!±  Bacrot - Vachier Lagrave, Bastia 2012. }
10. Nd2 { This is clearly the best try for White. } 10... Ne4 11. c5 Nxd6 12.
cxd6 Qb4
{ Hitting both the b2- and d6-pawns.   Black has also tried the computer move  12...h5!?  to enable ...Rh6xd6 but this is time consuming and leaves Black uncoordinated:  13.Bg2  Rh6  14.Qc2!  Rxd6  15.Rd1  with good compention in Fressinet - Dominguez Perez, Huaian 2016. }
13. Bg2 Qxb2
{ This pawn is less important than the d6-pawn, but  13...Qxd6  14.O-O  O-O  15.Ne4  Qe6  16.Nc3  b4  17.Nd5  gave White good compensation in Vallejo Pons - Leko, Reykjavik 2015. }
14. O-O Rxa2 15. Rxa2 Qxa2 16. Ne4 O-O
{ It's messy, but White did not really have enough for the pawns in Fressinet - Gelfand, Almaty blitz 2016. }
*

