[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 c5 2. g3 Nc6 3. c4 e5 4. Nc3 g6 5. Bg2 Bg7 6. O-O d6 7. Ne1 Be6 8. d3
Nge7 9. Nc2 d5
{ Black scores around 70% here!  As always we have to avoid   9...O-O  10.Ne3+= }
10. cxd5 Nxd5 11. Ne3 Nde7
{ Black has more space so he keeps pieces on the board. } 12. Ne4 b6 13. b4
{ 13.Qa4  Rc8=+   13.Ng5  Bd7=+ } 13... Nxb4
{ This sacrifice is sound, but   13...cxb4  N  14.a3  b3  15.Ng5  Bd7  16.Qxb3  O-O  =+  was good too. }
14. Ng5 Bd7 15. Bxa8 Qxa8 16. a4 h6 { Simpler was   16...Nec6 } 17. Ne4 Bh3 18.
a5 Qc6 19. axb6 axb6 20. Qa4 { after   20.Re1  f5  is strong } 20... Bxf1 21.
Kxf1 f5
{ a bit risky, but objectively best  Black is also better after   21...Qxa4  22.Rxa4  O-O }
22. Nd6+ Kd7 23. Nec4
{ White quickly runs out of steam after   23.Ndc4?  b5  24.Qa7+  Ke6-+ } 23...
e4
{ Black has played well, but the path is a narrow here.   23...Rb8!  24.Qa7+  Ke6  25.Kg1  Rd8 }
24. dxe4 b5 { Better was   24...fxe4  25.Bf4=∞ } 25. Nxb5 fxe4
{ The last chance was   25...Bxa1  26.Qa7+  Ke6  27.Nc7+  Kf7  28.Qxa1  28...Kg8□ }
26. Na5 Qf6 27. Nb3 Qc6 28. Be3 Bxa1 29. Nxc5+ Kd8 30. Qxa1 Rf8 31. Qa5+ Ke8
32. Qxb4 Nf5 33. Kg2 *

