Bg2 Nxc4 9. O-O d6
{ The most common move is   9...Be7  when  10.e4  d6  looks similar, but now  11.Qe2  hits our knight immediately. After }
10. e4 Bd7 { This allows Black to play a quick ...Rc8. } 11. Qe2
{ 11.a4  Rc8  12.a5  Qd8  13.a6  b5  14.Nd4  b4  15.Na4  Be7  16.b3  occurred in a blitz game Dubov - Vidit, Moscow @@StartBracket@@blitz@@EndBracket@@ 2019. Here  16...Nb6∓  would leave White with insufficient comepensation for the pawn. }
