1. Nf3 c5 2. c4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 6. Ndb5 d5 7. Bf4 e5 8.
cxd5 exf4 9. dxc6 bxc6 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8 11. O-O-O+ Ke7 12. Nd4
{ One of the points of Black's odd-looking king move is that   12.Nd6?  is not a good choice here because of  12...Be6  and Black is already better. }
12... Bd7 { Already the position is trending towards a black advantage. } 13.
e4
{ 13.g3?  fxg3  14.hxg3  Ng4  and White cannot guard the f2-pawn.   13.h3  g6  14.g3  fxg3  15.fxg3  Bg7  16.Bg2  Rhc8  17.Rhf1  Rab8=+  favors Black - White's two little trumps - a better pawn structure and slightly safer king - are gone, while Black retains the bishop pair and some initiative.   13.Nc2  is passive.  13...g6  14.e4  Ng4  15.Rd2  Bh6  16.h3  Ne5  17.f3  Rhd8=+  with the bishop pair and a great outpost on e5.   13.Rd3  was tried in one game, but it looks awkward. Black should play  13...Ng4!  14.Nd1  g6  with a good position. }
13... fxe3 14. Re1 Ng4 15. f3
{ 15.Ba6  15...g6!  Same story. The bishop will come to h6.  16.f3  Nf2  16...Bg7 is another good option.  17.Rhf1  Kf6  18.Nc2  Bh6  19.Nxe3  Rhe8  20.f4  Ng4  21.Nxg4+  Bxg4  22.g3=  With great care White has managed to equalize! I still like the bishops...   15.fxe3  g6=+  with ...Bh6 and ...Ne5 coming, is nice for Black.   15.h3?  hopes to lure the knight into trouble, but it does not work.  15...Nxf2  16.Rxe3+  Kd8  17.Rg1  Bc5-+  @@StartBracket@@a typical idea, as we shall see@@EndBracket@@ gives White insurmountable problems. }
15... Nf2 16. Rg1
{ runs into   16.Rxe3+  Kd8  17.Rg1  Bc5!  again  18.Nce2  Re8  19.Rxe8+  Kxe8∓  with the bishop pair and more active position. }
16... Kf6 17. Nc2 { 17.Rxe3  Bc5  again } 17... Re8 18. g3
{ 18.Nxe3  Bc5  19.Kd2  Re5  and ... Rhe8 } 18... a5
{ This looks like a waste of a tempo.  Stronger was   18...Bf5!  19.Rg2  @@StartBracket@@both captures on e3 run into 19...Bc5@@EndBracket@@  19...Bxc2  20.Rxf2   20.Kxc2  Bc5  Bf5!  21.Rg2  Bb4∓  which is great for Black. The e3-pawn still lives! }
19. Na4
{ 19.Nxe3!  Bc5  20.Kd2  20...Bc8  21.Rg2  Rd8+  22.Kc2  Rhe8  23.Rxf2  Rxe3  24.Rxe3  Bxe3  25.Ne4+  Kg6  26.Re2= }
19... g6 20. f4 { 20.Rxe3  Bh6  21.f4  g5→ } 20... Ng4 21. h3 Nf2 22. h4
{ 22.Rxe3  Rxe3  23.Nxe3  Nxh3 } 22... Ng4
{ 22...Bb4!?  23.Rxe3   23.Nxb4  axb4  Rxe3  24.Nxe3  Re8  25.Nc2  Bd6∓ } 23.
a3 Bf5 24. Bh3 Bxc2 25. Kxc2 Nf2 26. Bg2 Kf5 27. Bf3 { 27.Bxc6?  Rc8 } 27...
Re6 { 27...Re4!?  28.Bxe4+  Kxe4 } 28. Re2 Bg7 29. Nc5 Re7 30. Rge1 Rb8
